install docker vscode extension ==> code --install-extension ms-vscode-remote.remote-containers
open vscode
use remote containers in the bottom-left on vscode panel
choose Add Development Container Configuration Files... 
install liveserver
copy leaflet files
open docker desktop
vscode choose Reopen in Container 
the image is built
delete vscode container 
close docker desktop
vscode choose Reopen in local (it is normal environment)
in Terminal: pull vscode image ==> docker pull codercom/code-server
in Terminal: open vscode container ==>docker container run -d --name vscode -p 8080:8080 -e PASSWORD=YOUR_PASSWORD codercom/code-server:latest
open browser:localhost:8080
choose image leaflet
use to liveserver to open leaflet
done
